## Confidence Scoring Weights
When calculating/updating confidence scores, use these weights exactly:

| Step | Weight |
|------|--------|
| 0    | 20%    |
| 1    | 18%    |
| 2    | 15%    |
| 3    | 8% (optional, −8% if skipped) |
| 4    | 7% (optional, −7% if skipped) |
| 5    | 12%    |
| 6    | 5% (optional, −5% if skipped) |
| 7    | 10%    |
| 8    | 5%     |

Thresholds: `< 60%` = Low · `60–89%` = Medium · `≥ 90%` = Ready

---

## Hallucination Layers
8 layers must all pass before `[Submit for Approval]` is allowed.
Red layers = hard block that **cannot** be overridden by any user.

| Layer | Name | Triggers After |
|-------|------|---------------|
| 1 | Template Selection Validation | Step 1 |
| 2 | Scope Boundary Enforcement | Step 1 |
| 3 | Clause Library Matching | Step 7 |
| 4 | Cross-Step Consistency Check | Step 2 |
| 5 | Compliance Alignment | Step 7 |
| 6 | Prohibited Clause Detection | Step 7 (non-discrimination) |
| 7 | Business Context Anchoring | Step 0 |
| 8 | Evidence Pack Gate Validation | Step 4 |

